author = {McCagie Brooks Rogers},
abstract = {This article introduces the MYTHSEEKER project and MYTHSEEKER computer system. Both are concerned with computer-aided interactive exploration of traditional systems of personal myth and meditation. Imagery and sound are used for this purpose. Four major MYTHSEEKER software modules are defined that use interactive multimedia, expert systems, and virtual reality technologies. An introduction to the system concept is offered. History of the MYTHSEEKER project is briefly outlined, and technological, humanistic, and mythic/meditational interconnections of the disciplines involved are discussed. First-order requirements for the MYTHSEEKER system are offered under the categories function, methodology, data base, technology, and ethics. Second-order function and methodology requirements are then presented with examples for their realization, and second-order data base requirements are explicated. Implementation of MYTHSEEKER is outlined on a high level in terms of successions of interfaces, data structures, and generic module structures. Open issues are discussed. Two appendices provide, respectively, a summary of the MYTHSEEKER qualitative model needed for an integrated framework and an ethics statement for MYTHSEEKER application.}
}
